    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Deseed your<strong> pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into strips</p><p>Wash your<strong> pak choi</strong>, then cut<strong> </strong>in half, separating the <strong>white base</strong> and <strong>green tops</strong></p><p>Cut the <strong>white base</strong> into bite-sized pieces</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/thai-style-basa-and-veg-parcel-with-cauliflower-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Boil half a kettle</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/thai-style-basa-and-veg-parcel-with-cauliflower-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Roughly chop your <strong>creamed</strong> <strong>coconut</strong> (if required!) and dissolve it in 100ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><span class=\"text-purple\">[150ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>soy sauce</strong>, <strong>Thai green curry paste</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic</strong>,<strong> chopped ginger</strong>, 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and your <strong>lemongrass & lime leaf paste </strong>and stir it all up \u2013 this is your <strong>Thai-style curry stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/thai-style-basa-and-veg-parcel-with-cauliflower-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Cut A3 size sheet (1 per person) of <strong>baking paper</strong> (or tin foil)</p><p>Place the <strong>chopped pepper, chopped pak choi white base</strong> and the <strong>green tops</strong> in the middle of the sheet[s]</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/thai-style-basa-and-veg-parcel-with-cauliflower-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Lay your <strong>fish fillet[s] </strong>(1 per sheet)<strong> </strong>on top of the vegetables and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/thai-style-basa-and-veg-parcel-with-cauliflower-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Slightly scrunch the edges of the paper around the filling and then add the <strong>Thai-style curry stock</strong></p><p>Scrunch the edges of the <strong>baking paper</strong> together around the fish to form a sealed parcel[s] and add to a baking tray (or two!)</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 17 min or until the fish is cooked through and the veg has softened \u2013 this is your <strong>Thai-style fish & veg</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/thai-style-basa-and-veg-parcel-with-cauliflower-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>basmati rice</strong> and <strong>cauliflower rice </strong>to a pot with a lid with 160ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[250ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [300ml]</span> <strong>cold water </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/thai-style-basa-and-veg-parcel-with-cauliflower-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> Thai-style fish & veg </strong>with the <strong>cauliflower rice</strong> to the side</p><p>Tip: For fancy presentation, press the rice into a small bowl and turn out</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
